/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/theme_color\">theme_color</a></li></ol>\n","sidebarMacro":"QuickLinksWithSubpages","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  The <code>description</code> manifest member is used to explain the core features or functionality of your web application.\n  This text helps users understand your app's purpose when viewing it in an app store.\n</p>\n<div class=\"notecard note\">\n  <p><strong>Note:</strong> The <code>description</code> member is optional, and app stores may not use this text when presenting your app.</p>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><div class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">json</span></div><pre class=\"brush: json notranslate\"><code>\"description\": \"Track your daily tasks and plan your projects efficiently.\"\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"values","title":"Values","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"description\"><a href=\"#description\"><code>description</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>A string that describes your web app.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"description_2","title":"Description","isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  The <code>description</code> member is supplementary metadata that does not affect the app's runtime behavior or how browsers present the app.\n  Its value is used in app stores and other distribution platforms to help users understand what your app does.\n  Additionally, it provides an accessible description of your installed app.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"adding_a_description_for_a_meal_planning_web_app","title":"Adding a description for a meal planning web app","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Simple <code>description</code> in left-to-right language:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><div class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">json</span></div><pre class=\"brush: json notranslate\"><code>{\n  \"name\": \"Meal Planner\",\n  \"description\": \"Plan your weekly meals and automatically generate shopping lists. Track nutrition and discover recipes.\"\n}\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/manifest-app-info/#description-member","title":"Web App Manifest - Application Information"}],"query":"html.manifest.description"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"html.manifest.description"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Description","id":"description_2"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The description manifest member is used to explain the core features or functionality of your web application.\n  This text helps users understand your app's purpose when viewing it in an app store.","popularity":0.0018,"modified":"2020-10-15T22:19:35.118Z","other_translations":[],"pageType":"web-manifest-member","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/manifest/description","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/main/files/en-us/web/manifest/description/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/null","filename":"index.md"},"short_title":"description","parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"References"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest","title":"Web app manifests"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/description","title":"description"}],"pageTitle":"description - Web app manifests | MDN","noIndexing":false},"url":"/en-US/docs/Web/Manifest/description"}